      "content": "i get the mixed bag thing, but when u say it was a \"success\" in the short term because it removed gaddafi... isn't that a pretty narrow way to look at it? like, if the end result is just a failed state and more terrorism, doesn't that make the whole intervention a strategic failure regardless of what happened to the leader? wouldn't a realist argue the whole thing was just a mistake?",
